0.title: arnold press
0.description: This is a shoulder press that involves rotating the arms from a pronated to a supinated position

1.title: back extension
1.description: This is a lower back exercise in which the body is bent at the waist, typically over a hyperextension bench, exercise ball or other equipment

2.title: bench press
2.description: This is an exercise in which the weight is pressed upwards from a lying position on a bench

3.title: bicep curl
3.description: This is an exercise in which weight is pulled using the biceps muscle in a "curling" movement of the elbow

4.title: burpee
4.description: This is a cardio exercise which requires squatting down, kicking the feet back and extending the body, bringing the feet back in, then jumping straight up

5.title: cable crossover
5.description: This is an exercise in which the arms pull on cables, in an arc, until they meet in front of the chest.

6.title: calf raise
6.description: This is an exercise in which the body is pressed up solely through movement of the ankles, thus activating the calf muscles

7.title: clean
7.description: The lifter moves a barbell from the floor to a racked position across the deltoids

8.title: clean and jerk
8.description: The clean and jerk involves first lifting a barbell from the floor to the deltoids (clean), and then raising the barbell above the head, finishing with straight arms and legs (jerk)

9.title: crunch
9.description: An exercise in which the shoulders are lifted off the ground by contracting the abdominal muscles

10.title: deadlift
10.description: This is an exercise in which weight is pulled up by extending the hips and knee

11.title: bench dip
11.description: This is an exercise in which the body is hanging and supported by both arms holding on to parallel bars or other supporting structures. The body weight is lifted by pressing on the arms.

12.title: front raise
12.description: This is a shoulder exercise in which arms are lifted in an arc in front of the body, with the elbow angle kept constant

13.title: high knees
13.description: This is a cardio exercise which requires running by bringing the knees high so that the hip makes at least a right angle

14.title: hip extension
14.description: This is an exercise in which weight is pulled by extending the hip

15.title: hip raise
15.description: This is an exercise in which the hip is raised off the ground by contracting the abdominal muscles. The legs are kept in a fixed position.

16.title: jm press
16.description: This is a triceps exercise in which weight is pressed up from the chest mainly through an extension of the elbow, thus focusing on the triceps

17.title: jumping jack
17.description: This is a cardio exercise which requires jumping between a position with arms to the side and legs together to a second position with arms straight above the head and legs wide apart

18.title: lateral raise
18.description: This is a shoulder exercise in which arms are lifted laterally in an arc, with the elbow angle kept constant

19.title: hamstring curl
19.description: This is an exercise in which weight is pulled up with the legs by "curling" the knees

20.title: quad extension
20.description: This is an exercise in which weight is pushed up by extending the knees. It is usually performed in a seated position so that only the thighs are kept in a fixed position and only the lower leg moves.

21.title: leg raise
21.description: This is an exercise in which legs are raised up from a lying position while keeping knees and rest of the body straight

22.title: lunge
22.description: This is an exercise in which weight is pressed up from a position in which one leg is in front of the body with knee bent and foot flat on the ground, and the other leg is behind the body. The body is pressed up so that both knees are straightened.

23.title: pike press
23.description: This is a shoulder-activating exercise where the body weight is pressed upwards from a V body position

24.title: plank
24.description: This is an isometric exercise in which the body weight is supported by the arms and feet, and the upper body and legs are kept straightened and rigid, facing down, in a "plank" position

25.title: lat pulldown
25.description: This is a back exercise in which weight is pulled down from above the body, usually performed by pulling down on a cable

26.title: pullover
26.description: This is a chest exercise in which the weight is pulled over the head with elbows slightly bent

27.title: pullup
27.description: This is an exercise in which the body is suspended and the weight is pulled up by pulling on a bar. The hands grip the bar in an overhand fashion (the back of the hands facing the body).

28.title: pushup
28.description: The push-up is an exercise in which the body is lifted from a prone position by pressing with the arms

29.title: row
29.description: This is a back exercise in which weights and arms are pulled back towards the body

30.title: russian twist
30.description: The Russian Twist involves a repeated twisting motion of the abdomen

31.title: shoulder press
31.description: This is an exercise in which the weight is pressed straight upwards from the shoulders

32.title: side skaters
32.description: This is an exercise in which a lateral jump is performed, landing on one foot, with the alternate leg outstretched behind.

33.title: situp
33.description: An exercise in which the entire back is lifted off the ground by contracting the abdominal muscles

34.title: squat
34.description: This is an exercise in which the body weight is pushed up with the legs from a position with knees bent at a 90 degree angle

35.title: step up
35.description: This is an exercise in which the body weight is pushed up by stepping up into a higher platform with one leg

36.title: thruster
36.description: This is an exercise which involves pressing weight up with the legs from a bent-knee position and pressing the weight up by extending the arms

37.title: triceps extension
37.description: This is an exercise in which weight is pressed overhead by extending the elbows

38.title: v ups
38.description: This is an exercise in which both the entire back and the legs are lifted off the ground simultaneously, forming a "V" with the body

39.title: wall sit
39.description: This is an isometric exercise in which knees and hips are kept at right angles with the back against a wall

40.title: wide grip dip
40.description: This is an exercise in which the body is hanging and supported by both arms holding on to parallel bars or other supporting structures. The body weight is lifted by pressing on the arms.

41.title: basketball
41.description: A sport in which two teams try to shoot a ball into the opposing team's net.

42.title: biking
42.description: Strengthen your thighs and calve muscles by going on a bike ride!

43.title: boxing
43.description: A combat sport in which two people, usually wearing protective gloves and other protective equipment such as hand wraps and mouthguards, throw punches at each other for a predetermined amount of time in a boxing ring.

44.title: crossfit
44.description: A branded fitness regimen that has gained immense popularity, with workouts based on high intensity interval training

45.title: dancing
45.description: Uplift your mood and workout your entire body by dancing!

46.title: hiking
46.description: Strengthen your legs and build your stamina by exploring nature!

47.title: jump rope
47.description: Build muscle strength and endurance by jumping rope. Try different techniques!

48.title: kickboxing
48.description: Boxing in which boxers are permitted to kick with bare feet as in karate.

49.title: pilates
49.description: An exercise regimen that is typically performed on a floor mat or with the use of specialized apparatus and aims to improve flexibility and stability by strengthening the muscles and especially the torso-stabilizing muscles of the abdomen and lower back

50.title: rock climbing
50.description: The sport or activity of climbing rock faces, especially with the aid of ropes and special equipment.

51.title: running
51.description: The runner's high is no myth; build your endurance, strength, and stamina by going on a run.

52.title: swimming
52.description: Swimming builds endurance, muscle strength, and cardiovascular fitness. helps maintain a healthy heart and lungs!

53.title: walking
53.description: Improve your overall health by taking a walk! Improve your circulation, strengthen your muscles, and support your joints.

54.title: yoga
54.description: A group of physical, mental, and spiritual practices or disciplines which originated in ancient India, including breath control, simple meditation, and the adoption of specific bodily postures, is widely practiced for health and relaxation.

55.title: zumba
55.description: An aerobic fitness program featuring movements inspired by various styles of Latin American dance and performed primarily to Latin American dance music.
